Lindsay says an intermediate post at Lawrences creek 54 miles below Sioto and about 75 above Licking creek would be most essential. the principal war path crosses there from the Shawanese Wiandots & Northern Indians in general, and it is the only way a waggon road can be got from Kentucke up the Ohio.
A state of the Western posts & garrisons recommended by Col. Fleming

